voiceSpec.uploadSpec:
NEW FUNCTION in src/lib/upload.ts (NOTE: this file imports `{ supabase }` from './supabase' — match that, do NOT use getSupabaseBrowserClient):

export const VOICE_MAX_BYTES = 10 * 1024 * 1024; // also mirrored in constants.ts; keep one canonical in constants and import

export async function uploadAudio(blob: Blob, mimeType: string): Promise<string> {
  if (!supabase) {
    throw new Error('Supabase is not configured. Please set NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL and NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY environment variables.');
  }
  if (blob.size > 10 * 1024 * 1024) throw new Error('AUDIO_TOO_LARGE'); // defense in depth; editor already checks
  // Strip ;codecs=... so the contentType matches a plain mime (avoids bucket-allowlist rejection)
  const baseMime = (mimeType || blob.type || '').split(';')[0];
  const extByMime: Record<string,string> = {
    'audio/mp4':'m4a','audio/x-m4a':'m4a','audio/aac':'m4a',
    'audio/mpeg':'mp3','audio/webm':'webm','audio/ogg':'ogg','audio/wav':'wav','audio/x-wav':'wav',
  };
  const ext = extByMime[baseMime] || 'webm';
  const fileName = `${Date.now()}-${Math.random().toString(36).substring(2)}.${ext}`;
  const filePath = `voices/${fileName}`; // folder 'voices' — matches the bucket INSERT RLS policy
  const { error } = await supabase.storage
    .from('audio')
    .upload(filePath, blob, { contentType: baseMime || 'audio/webm', cacheControl: '3600' });
  if (error) throw new Error(`Upload failed: ${error.message}`);
  const { data } = supabase.storage.from('audio').getPublicUrl(filePath);
  return data.publicUrl;
}
// NO transcoding (no ffmpeg/wasm, no new npm dep). Store the recorded/uploaded container verbatim; the viewer sets <source type> from the stored mimeType. 60s + 10MB caps keep files ~1MB. iOS records audio/mp4→.m4a (the single most important mapping; plays on iOS natively).

BUCKET STRATEGY: NEW dedicated public `audio` bucket (NOT reuse of `images`). RATIONALE (verified): the `images` bucket has NO migration file in the repo — it was created via the Supabase dashboard, so its allowed_mime_types AND its INSERT RLS policy folder-scope are UNVERIFIABLE from code. cartoon-images (012) DOES folder-scope INSERT to (storage.foldername(name))[1]='originals'; if images is similarly scoped, every audio upload to it 403s in production. A dedicated `audio` bucket with its own voices/ folder policy is the only safe choice and faithfully mirrors the proven 012 precedent.

VALIDATION (single source of truth — constants.ts, enforced in editor BEFORE upload):
  VOICE_MAX_DURATION_SEC = 60; VOICE_MAX_SIZE_BYTES = 10*1024*1024;
  VOICE_ACCEPTED_EXT = /\.(mp3|m4a|wav|aac|ogg|webm)$/i
  Record path: MediaRecorder produces known-good blob; 60s cap enforced in-recorder; mime from blob.type post-stop.
  Upload path: accept attr pre-filters; runtime check isAcceptableAudio + size<=10MB + probed duration<=60s.

ORPHAN POLICY (documented, same as existing image flow): uploads happen at SUBMIT before onSave; a successful upload then tab-close orphans the object. We NEVER write a partial/unsaved reference to the DB. The voices/ folder layout is chosen so a future Vercel-cron GC (list audio/voices + cross-check against stories.content via service role) is trivial. Out of scope for v1.

